:: Gamesmith's Guild {"position":"950,1050","size":"100,100"}



:: connectfour {"position":"950,625","size":"100,100"}
<div style="text-align:center;"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Dahee-Hong/twine-assets/main/images/connectfourcensored.jpg" width="600">
</div>

Even for a game as simple as <span style="background-color:white; color:white;">████████████████████.</span>, I couldn't win at it.

Teasingly, 

She would always say that I'm

(align:"=><=")+(box:"X=")[(text-colour:red)[useless]]
(align:"=><=")+(box:"X=")[(text-colour:red)[selfish]]
(align:"=><=")+(box:"X=")[████████████████████]
(align:"=><=")+(box:"X=")[(text-colour:red)[difficult]]
(align:"=><=")+(box:"X=")[(text-colour:red)[i can't do anything right]]
(align:"=><=")+(box:"X=")[████████████████████]
(align:"=><=")+(box:"X=")[(text-colour:red)[i don't want to go [(text-colour:blue)[[there->student lounge]]]]]

stupid.


:: desk {"position":"500,275","size":"100,100"}
<div style="text-align:center;"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Dahee-Hong/twine-assets/refs/heads/main/images/deskedited.jpg" width="600">
</div>


I haven't been bothered to clean this since every day used to be hectic during the winter. 

I couldn't even have a moment of rest to take care of my dorm.

Now all I do is rest and I still don't have it in me to be tidy.

There are definitely things that can be thrown into the garbage. But what do I do about this [[doll]]? 

I can't think of a good reason to give it to her. 

I don't want to throw it away, but I don't want to see it anymore.


:: doll {"position":"500,425","size":"100,100"}
<div style="text-align:center;"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Dahee-Hong/twine-assets/refs/heads/main/images/dolledited.jpg" width="600">
</div>

I won this doll at the crane machine game at the basement of Homeplus. 

It took me about four tries before I finally knocked it into the prize vendor.

I want to give it to her to say sorry, but I don't even know how to muster the courage...

All I want to do is lay in my [[dorm room]]. 

(set: $visitedDoll to true)


:: dorm room {"position":"775,325","size":"100,100"}
<div style="text-align:center;"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Dahee-Hong/twine-assets/main/images/dormroomedited.jpg" width="600">
</div>

Just like any other morning these days, I wake up without an alarm.

There isn't anything needing my urgency and I can wake at my own pace.

I take a look at my phone with no notifications.

It's like any other day.

Everyone escapes Songdo by the time Saturday is around.

I don't blame them, Songdo can feel like hell if you've been here too long.

I take a gander around my unkempt room.

The garbage still hasn't been taken out, my [[desk]] has been unorganized since the start of last winter break.

I could do a reset and clean everything... but the weather is so nice today. If you take a peek outside the [[window]], you can see the cherry blossoms beginning to bloom.

(if: $visitedDoll is true and $visitedWindow is true)[I heard the [[student lounge->first floor]] is quite empty on Saturdays.
]


:: first floor {"position":"775,500","size":"100,100"}
<div style="text-align:center;"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Dahee-Hong/twine-assets/main/images/firstflooredited.jpg" width="600">
</div>

Freshman orientation was terrifying.

I couldn't help but think I wouldn't be able to make any friends or even just acquaintances.

It seemed that people made small cliques immediately and spent time during the small breaks we had.

The first floor is always a place of meeting and gathering, but I didn't feel that I belonged anywhere.

Yoonseul was the first one to talk to me as I wandered aimlessly during Freshman orientation.

She had asked me if I knew what was going, acting like she didn't know either.

I think she felt bad for me, but it felt like a warm light at the time.

Even now, I don't know why she chose me as someone to make a connection with.

I didn't know how lucky I was at the time. And how foolish I am now.

I was learning how to finally [[enjoy->student lounge]] time and feeling like I was wanted.


:: games lab {"position":"775,1175","size":"100,100"}



:: glassroom {"position":"775,1050","size":"100,100"}
Yoonseul was part of the student council, was a math tutor, and even was a teaching assistant for the art teacher.

She asked me if I did anything on campus and I couldn't really answer her.

Nothing, I just hang out with you, I would say.

I think it took her back abit, an aimless and lost boy that follows her around like a dog.

I took it upon my self to join something where I could make something and prove myself as someone who had actual ambition.

Surprisingly, I had no problem joining the [[Gamesmith's Guild]] at UAC.

After that, the [[games lab]] was like my second home.




:: student lounge {"position":"775,625","size":"100,100"}
<div style="text-align:center;"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Dahee-Hong/twine-assets/main/images/studentloungeedited.jpg" width="600">
</div>

I almost never studied or really cared to.

I didn't want to try so hard and academics were never serious to me.

But if it gave a reason for me to meet with Yoonseul, of course I would take it.

It felt so new to be around someone so bright at everything she does.

We used to hog the [[board games->connectfour]] and [[draw->whiteboard]] stupid things all the time. And of course, she won every game.

When she would get really excited and happy, she'd always dance and sing some song she saw off of Instagram reels.

It makes me wonder where she gets her energy from.


:: whiteboard {"position":"775,750","size":"100,100"}
<div style="text-align:center;"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Dahee-Hong/twine-assets/main/images/whiteboardcensored.jpg" width="600">
</div>


Yoonseul wrote something one of these days on the white board after beating me in ████████████████████. She was dancing and teased me for losing.

It made me feel quite <span style="background-color:white; color:white;">████████████████████.</span>

I think she wrote something along the lines of <span style="background-color:white; color:white;"> ████████████████████.</span>.

(set: $code to "")

I can't seem to remember.

