:: whiteboard reveal {"position":"775,900","size":"100,100"}
"Big adorable idiot".

I can certainly agree with the idiot part, I could never be as academically gifted as she could be but a part of me thought if I stuck with her then maybe I can be more smarter and more reliable. 

But that was farther from the [[truth->glassroom]].


:: window {"position":"975,225","size":"100,100"}
<div style="text-align:center;"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Dahee-Hong/twine-assets/refs/heads/main/images/windowedited.jpg" width="600">
</div>

The sky is clear and the sun glows brightly. For a place like Songdo, the day feels light and refreshing.

The courtyard and in front of the cafeteria is usually bustling with students during the weekday. 

I live on the lowest floor possible in the B dorm, the 4th floor, and I can hear the screams, the laughs, and the footsteps.

The complaints of having to go to class and the nights where people come back from Triple Street having a little bit too much to drink.

Nowadays, people like taking pictures together at the big cherry blossom trees beside the dorm buildings.

It's days like these where I wish I can go back and laugh with them too.

These days I'm sitting in my [[dorm room]] waiting for nothing.

(set: $visitedWindow to true)


